Installation Steps:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa160\sl259\slmult0\b0\fs22 Go through these steps for complete installation of ROS- {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://wiki.ros.org/noetic/Installation/Ubuntu }}{\fldrslt{https://wiki.ros.org/noetic/Installation/Ubuntu\ul0\cf0}}}}\b\f0\fs24\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0\fs22 Build Rplidar ros package- \b\fs24\par

\pard\sa160\sl259\slmult0\b0\fs22                1) Create a catkin's workspcae.\b\fs24\par
\b0\fs22                2) Clone this project to your catkin's workspace src folder\par
                   ({{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://github.com/robopeak/rplidar_ros }}{\fldrslt{https://github.com/robopeak/rplidar_ros\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs22 )\par
               3) Running catkin_make to build rplidarNode and rplidarNodeClient\par
\b Run rplidar ros package\b0\par
There're two ways to run rplidar ros package\par
I. Run rplidar node and view in the rviz\par
roslaunch rplidar_ros view_rplidar.launch\par
You should see rplidar's scan result in the rviz.\par
II. Run rplidar node and view using test application\par
roslaunch rplidar_ros rplidar.launch \par
rosrun rplidar_ros rplidarNodeClient\par
You should see rplidar's scan result in the console\par
