\b\fs24 RPLidar SDK Installation (Windows)\b0\fs22\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa160\sl259\slmult0 Download RPLidar A1M8 SDK package (The lidar we are using for this project through through {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://www.slamtec.ai/ }}{\fldrslt{https://www.slamtec.ai/\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs22 . Slamtec provides usermanual, rplidarkit, datasheet and many more on various lidars.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Install a driver- CP210xVCPInstaller_x64 from SDK package\par

\pard\sa160\sl259\slmult0                (rplidar_sdk\\rplidar_sdk-master\\tools\\cp2102_driver\\CP210x_Windows_Drivers)\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa160\sl259\slmult0 Connect rplidar to the system using USB cable, then you should see the port in the device manager. (Make sure you select right COM port)\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Then you should see an application of UI representing the lidar.\par

